    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "LipidMatch currently has over 250,000 lipid species spanning 56 lipid types contained in in silico fragmentation libraries. With 56 lipid types, LipidMatch in silico libraries cover the greatest number of lipid types of any open source software to date, with MS-DIAL containing 34 lipid types, and Greazy containing 24 lipid types.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper documents 250,000+ species and 56 types as of 2017 publication. The card specifies thresholds of 500,000 species and 60 types, which are not supported by the paper. The paper does not describe a task to validate these higher thresholds or generate such a report.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s12859-017-1744-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Summary report documenting distinct lipid species count, distinct lipid-type category count, and threshold validation (\u2265500,000 species, \u226560 types)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:08:07.807631+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card's research question and expected outputs specify thresholds (500,000 species, 60 types) that are substantially higher than what the paper documents (250,000 species, 56 types). This suggests either: (1) the card reflects a later version of LipidMatch not described in this 2017 paper, or (2) the extractor conflated aspirational/future goals with documented capabilities.",
        "The paper does not describe a task to validate library coverage against specific thresholds or to generate a 'summary report' with threshold validation. The paper reports library statistics as part of its methods/results, but does not frame this as a reproducible task with pass/fail criteria.",
        "No mention of 'GitHub repository' appears in the paper; the paper references http://secim.ufl.edu/secim-tools/ as the distribution site."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
