    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_004/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "LipidMatch libraries are static excel files, as with all four software previously mentioned, the user can select which lipid types to query using LipidMatch... LipidMatch contains all lipid types in MS-DIAL 2.24, as well as LipidBlast release 3 development libraries... the user can select which lipid types to query using LipidMatch, hence limiting searches only to biologically relevant or expected lipid types and reducing run time. LipidMatch libraries contain only exact m/z values of precursors and fragment ions, making it relatively trivial for users to generate in silico libraries and/or convert other databases to the LipidMatch library format.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly states that users can develop and integrate custom libraries, and that the library format is trivial to generate.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s12859-017-1744-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_004",
