    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/file-format-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "LipidMatch libraries can be developed using LipidBlast Templates [11] or as explained in video tutorial 6 found in the Additional file 1. Each library should be developed with the correct annotation based on the structural resolution that can be inferred by fragments chosen for the identification criteria.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms users can develop custom libraries and provides guidance on format/annotation requirements.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s12859-017-1744-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "file-format-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Verify that a user-authored .csv lipid library conforms to LipidMatch's manual format specification before integration into the matching workflow.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:12:00.470178+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/file-format-validation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In silico libraries were developed in Excel as described in video tutorial 6 in the Additional file 1. Briefly, an R script was used to generate a list of possible fatty acid combinations for acyl containing lipids with 2 or 3 fatty acids.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes library development process with m/z fragmentation patterns and integration into LipidMatch.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s12859-017-1744-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "file-format-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "custom lipid entries with annotated m/z fragmentation patterns are correctly recognized and registered into the active library index",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:12:00.470178+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/file-format-validation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "LipidMatch libraries are static excel files, as with all four software previously mentioned, the user can select which lipid types to query using LipidMatch, hence limiting searches only to biologically relevant or expected lipid types and reducing run time. LipidMatch libraries contain only exact m/z values of precursors and fragment ions, making it relatively trivial for users to generate in silico libraries and/or convert other databases to the LipidMatch library format.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms users can author libraries and describes the format (exact m/z values of precursors and fragments).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s12859-017-1744-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "file-format-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have authored a custom .csv lipid library and need to confirm it adheres to LipidMatch's documented schema before placing it in the designated library directory",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:12:00.470178+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
