      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragmentation-pattern-annotation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In silico libraries were developed in Excel as described in video tutorial 6 in the Additional file 1. Briefly, an R script was used to generate a list of possible fatty acid combinations for acyl containing lipids... LipidMatch libraries contain only exact m/z values of precursors and fragment ions, making it relatively trivial for users to generate in silico libraries and/or convert other databases to the LipidMatch library format.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Excel/CSV format for library development and that users can create custom libraries.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s12859-017-1744-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragmentation-pattern-annotation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "structuring experimental or theoretical fragmentation data into machine-readable .csv library entries",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:12:14.530154+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragmentation-pattern-annotation/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "LipidMatch currently has over 250,000 lipid species spanning 56 lipid types contained in in silico fragmentation libraries.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper states 250,000+ lipid species, not 500,000+. The card overstates the built-in library size.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s12859-017-1744-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragmentation-pattern-annotation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You have custom lipid species (not covered by the 500,000+ built-in LipidMatch entries)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:12:14.530154+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragmentation-pattern-annotation/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For each lipid class, structurally indicative fragments were compiled using other MS/MS databases (LIPID MAPS, LipidBlast, and MS-DIAL), literature, and/or experimentally derived fragmentation. Using multiple sources to obtain fragmentation allowed for cross-validation of fragments and generation of lipid class-specific fragmentation rules.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes obtaining fragmentation patterns from literature, databases, and experimental sources.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s12859-017-1744-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragmentation-pattern-annotation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "availability of annotated m/z fragmentation patterns for your lipid of interest\u2014either from literature, prior experiments, or in-silico prediction",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:12:14.530154+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragmentation-pattern-annotation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "LipidMatch was developed and tested using data acquired from a Q-Exactive orbitrap mass spectrometer (Thermo Scientific, San Jose, CA). LipidMatch has also been tested using data acquired on an Agilent 6540 Q-TOF (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA). LipidMatch can be used with a variety of other vendors and data formats.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not explicitly state that Waters instruments are unsupported. It mentions Thermo and Agilent support and states 'variety of other vendors' without naming Waters as excluded.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s12859-017-1744-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragmentation-pattern-annotation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Your MS/MS data is from a Waters instrument; LipidMatch does not currently support Waters files.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:12:14.530154+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/fragmentation-pattern-annotation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "[SUBSTRING-MATCH for LipidMatch | role: primary tool] LipidMatch uses rule-based identification. For each lipid type, the user can select which fragments must be observed for identification... Each fragment is assigned 1 if it is above the user defined minimum intensity and scans threshold and 0 if the fragment does not meet these criteria or was not found within the m/z tolerance.",
      "asbval:note": "LipidMatch confirmed as the primary matching tool that loads libraries and matches fragments.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1186-s12859-017-1744-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "fragmentation-pattern-annotation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "LipidMatch as primary tool for loading, integrating, and matching custom .csv lipid libraries against experimental MS/MS fragment m/z values",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:12:14.530154+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
