      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "LipidMatch libraries are static excel files, as with all four software previously mentioned, the user can select which lipid types to query using LipidMatch... LipidMatch libraries contain only exact m/z values of precursors and fragment ions, making it relatively trivial for users to generate in silico libraries and/or convert other databases to the LipidMatch library format.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms LipidMatch accepts user-generated libraries in Excel/CSV format and uses exact m/z matching.",
